survey_response.review_text: I was suffering from chronic cough for the last 2.5 months. I took treatment from a reputed pulmonologist after 1 month of self medication, but my condition was worsening. I decided to go to my native 2 days before my children's scool reopening. All of a sudden it struck me that I can meet an ENT once before leaving. It was a Saturday evening so none of the ENTs nearby were available. Luckily Dr Rakhee at Amar Jyoti nursing home was available. I met her and she calmly listened to my complaints, diagnosed my problem and gave me the right treatment. Within 5 days, there was 90 percentage improvement in my condition. Iam really grateful to Dr Rakhee. She is an excellent doctor and I genuinely recommend her based on my life saving experience

survey_response.review_text: HI. I visited this doctor and I am forced to write this as I was provoked by this lady's inappropriate behaviour . I went for a thumb cut , beware , the other lady will not properly give the x-ray report to which I became doubtful. The doc Rakhee suggested to go for a surgeon opinion. I honestly thought it will come under consulting. When I reached the next day , the receptionist told me to pay 500 and I said no I didn't know i have to pay and I was leaving in anger . SHE SHOULD INFORM POLICIES AND OTHER THING RIGHT AWAY. To which the doc Rakee and we spoke in the phone and her words were 'shouting and screaming ' , you have to pay , you have to pay . We have called him for you only. I said why are you forcing me. This is not a way to speak. She didn't let me speak at all. I asked can I atleast meet you as I'm eligible for it. She started screaming again ',that she has come for her son , her son is sick or she was with some patient. I am okay with anything *** *** **** ********** *** *** *** *** ***** ****** **** *** ****** *** **** No matter what , I will never ever vist this ******* ****** *** hospital ever. **** * *** ** ******  Till the end she screamed and the people infront of me just watched me and told me rudely that , don't speak anything just go, when I was trying to explain . The surgeon standing there was polite enough to let me speak and he said go on its okay and I said she was forcing me to pay. I didn't know . I was not using the service in the beginning anyway , they stopped me else I was gone. ** *** ****** * ***** ********** *** ** * **** ***** ***** * **** * **** ******* *** *** ****** ***** ****** *** ********* P.s I will never ever recommend this hospital and the doctor EVER .

survey_response.review_text: She was in a hurry. The call was scheduled at 10. She called around 10.15 after so many chats and reminders. I had Lready shared the report with her, ***** *** *** ******* ***** **** ** *** ************* The consultation fee was 600 rupees  the call was hardly for 8 minutes. When I asked about the diet, she told to check in internet.  I could have checked everything in internet  what's is the point of consulting the doctor then. I was asking something and she disconnected thr call. We treat doctors as God specially during this covid time. But it's so dissapointing.

review.practice_name: Amar Jyoti Nursing Home And P M P Medical Centre

survey_response.review_text:
My Daughter fell sick due to continuous fever in Bangalore, when she was staying alone in a hostel and was referred to Dr. Raakhee Padival in OPD, She attended her and did the initial diagnostic through blood test and found she was infested with Typhoid fever. 
Immediately, I was called and she explained about the case, rightfully advised to admit for treatment. My daughter was treated well with continuous attention, explaining every treatment and what to expect after every stage.
They attended her independently providing all right treatments, till I reached Bangalore the next day. 
When I reached next day she was better and the treatment continued for one more day and my daughter was released fully fit.
